Prerequisites:
Ensure the following are installed on your system:

1. PHP
2. cURL: This is typically included with PHP, but you may need to enable it in your php.ini configuration file.

Enabling cURL in PHP (if not already enabled)
1. Locate your php.ini file. 
2. Open the php.ini file in a text editor and uncomment ;extension=curl by removing the semicolon (;) at the beginning
3. Save the changes and restart your PHP service.

Instruction to run the PHP script:
php retrieve_dns_domains_records.php